11201612.name: Goorooyarroo Track
11201612.description: Pass through box—gum grassy woodland. Side trips from this track include: The Dams Valley, Old Joe Hill, Dunnarts Flat via McKeahnies Track and Gooroo Hill. The Goorooyarroo Track ends at the Mulligans Flat boundary so return the way you came in.

11201613.name: North Mulligans Circuit
11201613.description: This circuit provides sweeping views of Gungahlin and New South Wales. Kangaroo Grass dominates the lower slopes while steeper slopes support Red Stringybark Forest.

11201614.name: Mulligans Circuit
11201614.description: Meander through forest, woodland and grassy glades for an excellent overview of Mulligans Flat.

11201615.name: Mulligans Bird Walk
11201615.description: An enjoyable walk through box—gum grassy woodland with patches of forest. Many birds can be observed at the dams. A self-guide brochure is available on-site for this walk.
